A Russian lady, Marina, has expressed undying love for the songs of popular singer, songwriter and instrumentalist, Chinedu Izuchukwu Ololi, popularly known as Flavour N’abania or simply Flavour. She got two tattoos of his face on her body to demonstrate her affection. The Moscow-based lady revealed that she has been a fan of Flavour for a long time and loves his music. Showing off her tattoos in a video making rounds on social media, she said she got the first tattoo of the highlife singer’s face on her shoulder in 2015 and the second done a few years after. Marina hailed the ‘Ada’ hitmaker as the best musician in the world and she excitedly flaunted the tattoos both on her right arm as she expresses her love for him.